Hassan Sule, the first son of Abdullahi Sule, governor of Nasarawa State, has suddenly died, aged 36. Hassan, who got married to his first wife, Hajiya Sule, in June last year, died in Lafia, the state capital, in the late hours of Thursday, January 26, 2023. However, the death was not made public until this morning via a statement signed by the Governor’s Chief Press Secretary, Ibrahim Addra. The statement reads: “His Excellency, Abdullahi A. Sule, the Governor of Nasarawa State, on behalf of his family, announces the sudden demise of his son, Hassan Sule, whose sad event occurred on Thursday January 26, 2023. “Hassan died at the age of 36. “The late Hassan will be laid to rest in Gudi, Akwanga Local Government Area today, Friday at 10am.” 